\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
6.
 Policy Statement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Public trust in the administration of government technology requires that all personnel maintain the highest standards of professional conduct and integrity.
 All directives in this policy apply to all personnel within the scope defined in Section 2.
 Where a directive applies to a narrower audience,
 the specific role is identified.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.1 Adoption of Professional Standards
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Elko County Information Operations formally adopts the ACM Code of Ethics and Professional Conduct as the baseline for professional behavior.
 Personnel shall uphold the principles of contributing to human well-being,
 avoiding harm,
 and respecting privacy.
 Where the ACM Code and County or Department policy conflict,
 applicable State and Federal law shall take precedence,
 followed by County and Department policy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.2 Professional Conduct and Culture
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Respect in Communication
\series default
:
 Mocking,
 belittling,
 or dismissive comments regarding end-users,
 colleagues,
 or other departments—
whether verbal,
 written,
 or in digital chats—
is prohibited.
 Operational frustration does not justify unprofessional conduct.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
User-Centered Service
\series default
:
 Personnel shall respond to service requests and inquiries from County staff in a professional and courteous manner.
 Dismissive or condescending responses to end-user communications are prohibited.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Representation
\series default
:
 Personnel shall not express personal opinions as official County positions in any public forum or media channel unless explicitly authorized by the County Manager or IT Director.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Compliance with Personnel Policies
\series default
:
 Personnel shall comply with the Elko County Personnel Policies and applicable Collective Bargaining Agreements in addition to this policy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.3 Integrity and Conflict of Interest
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Zero-Gift Policy
\series default
:
 Personnel are strictly prohibited from accepting any gifts,
 gratuities,
 meals,
 entertainment,
 or favors from current or prospective technology vendors,
 regardless of monetary value.
 This includes standard industry courtesies such as vendor-paid business lunches or promotional items.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Rationale
\series default
:
 This standard is intentionally stricter than the minimum requirements of NRS 281A (Ethics in Government) to eliminate ambiguity and protect personnel from even the appearance of impropriety.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Vendor Interaction
\series default
:
 When meeting with vendors over a meal,
 personnel shall pay for their own share or expense it through official County channels if applicable.
 The vendor is never permitted to pay.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Truthfulness
\series default
:
 Personnel shall be honest in all professional reporting.
 Falsifying logs,
 obscuring errors,
 or misrepresenting the status of a project or system is a violation of this policy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.4 Stewardship of Information and Assets
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Confidentiality
\series default
:
 Personnel shall protect sensitive data (PII,
 PHI,
 CJIS) in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.11"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Data Governance and Classification Policy).
 Curiosity is not a valid reason for accessing data;
 access is permitted only for specific business duties.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Zero Tolerance for Misuse
\series default
:
 The use of County IT assets for harassment,
 illegal activity,
 or personal financial gain is strictly prohibited.
\end_layout

